Phone lines at the Kariega police station  will be down this weekend due to scheduled maintenance and upgrades to the telephone system. The lines are expected to be down from Friday to Monday. The police asked for  the residents' patience and said all emergency calls could be made on 082-301-7804. Alternatively, the 10111 centre may be contacted. However,  police would be on duty at the  station throughout the weekend. HeraldLIVE